30/07/2003
MELJINE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The Supreme Defence Council of Serbia-Montenegro decided on Tuesday (29 July) to dismiss Maj Gen Radoslav Skoric, head of the federal military intelligence service.
The service is responsible for gathering information on foreign armed forces.
The council also endorsed a defence ministry proposal to retire several ranking army officials as part of an ongoing effort to restructure and reform the military.
(B92, Tanjug - 29/07/03)
